The paper deals with a coding scheme for storing information in flash memories, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of information theory (cs.IT). The proposed encoding procedure involves manipulating the ranks of cells, which is a problem in data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses upper bounds and code constructions, which are topics in coding theory (cs.SI) and computer architecture (cs.AR).
